{
  "text": "Colorimetric MTT assay was performed to determine antileishmanial activity of different extracts of sea cucumber and drug control. After the incubation periods at 24 ± 2 ∘ C for 24, 48, and 72 hours, 25 L of syringe filtrated MTT work solution (5 mg/mL) was added to wells and incubated at 24 ± 2 ∘ C for 4 hours. The supernatants were removed completely without interrupting the cell sediments, and 100 L of dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO) was added to each well. After the microplate shaking for 15 min, the absorbance was recorded at 570 nm on a microplate reader. The viability of treated and untreated promastigotes was studied by measuring conversion of MTT to the reduced form that indicates cell viability, and a decline in the amount of MTT alteration is a toxicity indication to the promastigotes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Relative numbers of viable cells are prescribed by the following equation:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "31829786",
